                                                                                            <p><strong>Emily Doyle</strong>’s debut collection, <em>Please Don’t Touch the Body</em>, and debut novel, <em>Encounter</em>, are forthcoming from Bloomsbury. Her work has appeared in <em>Ploughshares</em>, <em>Kenyon Review</em>, <em>The Sun</em>, and <em>elsewhere</em>, and she has received numerous awards and fellowships, including the Bread Loaf–Rona Jaffe Scholarship, the Abraham Lincoln Polonsky Endowed Award, and the H. W. Hill Scholarship. She lives in Los Angeles.&nbsp;</p>
